", "computed_md5": "08a49193efdb39748aa48ffa712822a3", "mimetype": "application/vnd.ms-excel"}, {"id": 36952425, "name": "Table_8.xls", "size": 5632, "is_link_only": false, "download_url": "https://ndownloader.figshare.com/files/36952425", "supplied_md5": "7f6618155b6988dfbead7de50d41ddbc", "computed_md5": "7f6618155b6988dfbead7de50d41ddbc", "mimetype": "application/vnd.ms-excel"}], "folder_structure": {}, "authors": [{"id": 13525548, "full_name": "J\u00e9ssica Cerutti de Oliveira", "first_name": "J\u00e9ssica Cerutti de", "last_name": "Oliveira", "is_active": false, "url_name": "_", "orcid_id": ""}, {"id": 13525551, "full_name": "Glaucia Helena Gon\u00e7alves", "first_name": "Glaucia Helena", "last_name": "Gon\u00e7alves", "is_active": false, "url_name": "_", "orcid_id": ""}, {"id": 12816917, "full_name": "Dayane Melo Campos", "first_name": "Dayane Melo", "last_name": "Campos", "is_active": false, "url_name": "_", "orcid_id": ""}, {"id": 13525554, "full_name": "Daniela Lemes Ferreira", "first_name": "Daniela Lemes", "last_name": "Ferreira", "is_active": false, "url_name": "_", "orcid_id": ""}, {"id": 13525557, "full_name": "Nathany Clara da Silva", "first_name": "Nathany Clara da", "last_name": "Silva", "is_active": false, "url_name": "_", "orcid_id": ""}, {"id": 4432549, "full_name": "Juliana Hotta Ansai", "first_name": "Juliana Hotta", "last_name": "Ansai", "is_active": false, "url_name": "_", "orcid_id": ""}], "custom_fields": [{"name": "Read full text", "value": ["http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S1809-29502022000200145&lng=en&tlng=en"], "settings": {"placeholder": "Read full text", "is_multiple": false}, "field_type": "url", "order": null, "is_mandatory": false}], "figshare_url": "https://scielo.figshare.com/articles/dataset/Monthly_phone_calls_and_calendars_to_record_falls_rate_in_community-dwelling_older_adults_included_in_a_randomized_clinical_trial/20729013", "download_disabled": false, "description": "<p></p><p>ABSTRACT This longitudinal study aimed to analyze monthly phone calls and calendars as a mean to record falls rate in community-dwelling older adults over 22 weeks, and to verify factors related to adherence to the falls calendar. Participants underwent an assessment composed by anamnesis, level of physical activity, neuropsychological measures, and mobility. They also received a schedule of falls that should be completed over 22 weeks, on the day(s) a fall occurred. Moreover, the volunteers received monthly phone calls to inquire about occurrence of falls over time. For data analysis, a \u03b1=0.05 significance level was adopted and the SPSS software (20.0) was used to perform statistical tests. The two tools were compared regarding \u201csensitivity\u201d and \u201cspecificity.\u201d In total, 52 older adults composed the final sample, with a mean age of 70.5 years old. The adherence to the calendar was 63.4% compared to phone calls. Of nine participants who reported falls by phone calls, three notified them in the calendar, resulting in a 33% sensitivity. Out of the 43 people who did not report falls by phone calls, 31 delivered the calendar without registration. Thus, the specificity of the calendar was 72%. Schooling level, Mini Mental State Exam score and the Addenbrooke\u2019s Cognitive Examination (revised version) score significantly influenced adherence to the calendar. In conclusion, there was a greater registration of falls by the monthly phone call compared to the calendar tool in community-dwelling older adults.</p><p></p>", "funding": null, "funding_list": [], "version": 1, "status": "public", "size": 2929172, "created_date": "2022-08-30T08:12:52Z", "modified_date": "2023-06-03T06:37:33Z", "is_public": true, "is_confidential": false, "is_metadata_record": false, "confidential_reason": "", "metadata_reason": "", "license": {"value": 1, "name": "CC BY 4.0", "url": "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"}, "tags": ["Aging", "Accidental Falls", "Preventive Health Services"], "keywords": ["Aging", "Accidental Falls", "Preventive Health Services"], "categories": [{"id": 314, "title": "Orthopaedics", "parent_id": 142, "path": "", "source_id": "", "taxonomy_id": 10}, {"id": 321, "title": "Rehabilitation and Therapy (excl. Physiotherapy)", "parent_id": 142, "path": "", "source_id": "", "taxonomy_id": 10}], "references": ["https://doi.org/10.1590/1809-2950/20032229022022pt"], "has_linked_file": false, "citation": "Oliveira, J\u00e9ssica Cerutti de; Gon\u00e7alves, Glaucia Helena; Campos, Dayane Melo; Ferreira, Daniela Lemes; Silva, Nathany Clara da; Ansai, Juliana Hotta (2022). Monthly phone calls and calendars to record falls rate in community-dwelling older adults included in a randomized clinical trial. SciELO journals. Dataset. https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.20729013.v1", "related_materials": [{"id": 35106851, "identifier": "10.1590/1809-2950/20032229022022pt", "title": "Monthly phone calls and calendars to record falls rate in community-dwelling older adults included in a randomized clinical trial", "relation": "IsSupplementTo", "identifier_type": "DOI", "is_linkout": true, "link": "https://doi.org/10.1590/1809-2950/20032229022022pt"}], "is_embargoed": false, "embargo_date": null, "embargo_type": null, "embargo_title": "", "embargo_reason": "", "embargo_options": [], "id": 20729013, "title": "Monthly phone calls and calendars to record falls rate in community-dwelling older adults included in a randomized clinical trial", "doi": "10.6084/m9.figshare.20729013.v1", "handle": "", "url": "https://api.figshare.com/v2/articles/20729013", "published_date": "2022-08-30T08:12:52Z", "thumb": "https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/ppreviews-scielo-87127105408/36952392/thumb.png", "defined_type": 3, "defined_type_name": "dataset", "group_id": 12817, "url_private_api": "https://api.figshare.com/v2/account/articles/20729013", "url_public_api": "https://api.figshare.com/v2/articles/20729013", "url_private_html": "https://figshare.com/account/ar